-- Maridive & Oil of Egypt Raised to `Buy' at EFG on Global Industry Outlook
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2010-11-11T08:12:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/maridive-oil-of-egypt-raised-to-buy-at-efg-on-global-industry-outlook.html
Maridive & Oil Services, an Egyptian
oil services company, was raised to “buy” from “neutral” at
EFG-Hermes Holding SAE, citing a “more positive” global
industry outlook.  “We are now more confident that the industry is entering
into a recovery phase and expect Maridive to announce new
contract awards, which will improve earnings visibility,”
Dubai-based analysts Abid Riaz and Nadine Hassouna wrote in a
reported today.  They set the share-price estimate at $3.92. The stock
closed at $3.22 in Cairo yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
